SIMPLE: womb
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Womb
<hw>Womb</hw> <pr>(w⟦oomac⟧m)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>wombe</ets>, <ets>wambe</ets>, AS. <ets>wamb</ets>,
<ets>womb</ets>; akin to D. <ets>wam</ets> belly, OS. & OHG.
<ets>wamba</ets>, G. <ets>wamme</ets>, <ets>wampe</ets>, Icel.
<ets>v⟦oum⟧mb</ets>, Sw. <ets>v⟦aring⟧mb</ets>, Dan. <ets>vom</ets>,
Goth. <ets>wamba</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The belly; the
abdomen.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And he coveted to fill his <qex>woman</qex> of the cods that the
hogs eat, and no man gave him.</q> <rj><qau>Wyclif (Luke xv.
16).</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>An I had but a belly of any indifferency, I were simply the most
active fellow in Europe. My <qex>womb</qex>, my <qex>womb</qex>, my
<qex>womb</qex> undoes me.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The uterus. See
<er>Uterus</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The place where anything is generated or
produced.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>womb</qex> of earth the genial seed receives.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Any cavity containing and enveloping
anything.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The center spike of gold⟦br⟧
Which burns deep in the bluebell's <qex>womb</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>R.
Browning.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Womb</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Womb
<hw>Womb</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To inclose in a womb, or as in a
womb; to breed or hold in secret.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wombat</ent>⟦br⟧
